{"key":"processedPost-5246529","value":{"id":5246529,"first":5244467,"last":5247467,"when":1138733139,"utime":"01/31/06 08:45 PM","content":"Make your greenhouse loose and airy.  There is no need to seal it up tight.  The more holes the better.  They will provide air exchange.  A cool mist humidifier sitting on a shelf inside will maintain humidity.  If you try to seal it up and make the thing air tight, you'll have nothing but problems.  Bear in mind, greenhouses are for bulk substrates with casing layers.  Try to keep humidity in the 80% range.  For cakes you need much higher humidity, so stick with a terrarium.<br />RR","title":"Re: trying to find greenhouse in winter","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}